    "body": "In addition to smartpy being out of date, I'm unable to use the `truffle@tezos` toolset on my Mac M1 chipset because the Docker image the `truffle compile` command relies on is compiled for `linux/amd64` when I require a `linux/arm64` build.\r\n\r\nAs a potential workaround, I've re-build the Docker image with the latest version for my chipset, but have yet to figure out a way to configure the tooling to use it. Is there a way to specify a local Docker image?\r\n\r\nAs a user, it would be a lot easier for me to simply use my local smartpy-cli install and configure truffle to use that.\r\n\r\nRelated issue: https://github.com/trufflesuite/SmartPyBasic-Docker/issues/3",
